  "verdict": "KEEP-IN-QUARANTINE",
  "verdict_reason": "The fix is real: the scale-out now fires (candidate 116 trades vs parent 96 = +20 one-shot half-exits), so v2 is a genuine divergence, not v1's phantom tie. What the divergence buys is RISK-ADJUSTED, not additive: candidate median Sharpe is higher at every cost (+0.095 @2bps, +0.092 @5bps, +0.092 @10bps) and the worst window improves by a large +0.40pp at every cost (2022-H1 bear: -0.98% -> -0.58%). But it does this by SHAVING RETURN, not adding edge. Median return is essentially flat (-0.0075pp @2bps, -0.0045pp @5bps, +0.002pp @10bps) and MEAN return is clearly LOWER at every cost (-0.11 to -0.12pp) because the half-exit caps the fat right tail (2026-recent bull +3.29% -> +1.87%; 2024-Q2 bull +0.73% -> +0.39%, which also drops it below BH-SPY and cuts pct_beat_bh from 0.875 -> 0.75 @2bps). Regime split is textbook scale-out: HELPS in bear (+0.24pp ret, +0.39 Sharpe avg over 2 windows) and chop (+0.04pp ret, +0.26 Sharpe), HURTS in bull (-0.39pp ret, -0.08 Sharpe over 4 windows). It is NOT a uniform improvement. Against the live mutation gate it FAILS: it does not clear MUTATION_MIN_DELTA_PCT=+0.10pp on median return at ANY cost (it is flat-to-negative there); it only clears the Sharpe-no-degradation rail (which it actually improves). A mutation that raises Sharpe purely by clipping the upside it already had \u2014 with no net median/mean return gain and a real cost in bull regimes and BH-relative win rate \u2014 is a risk-preference re-parameterization, not discovered alpha. That is exactly the 'raises Sharpe by shaving return' case the directive says to call out, so it does not earn promotion over simply holding (the parent). KEEP-IN-QUARANTINE rather than REJECT because the drawdown/worst-window improvement is real and consistent (+0.40pp worst window, every cost), and a future variant with a HIGHER trigger (e.g. trim at p75 +4.11% instead of the median +2.60% so it stops clipping the median winners and only de-risks the genuine outliers) could plausibly keep the bear/chop drawdown benefit while giving back less bull upside. WHAT WOULD CHANGE THE CALL: median return delta >= +0.10pp at >=2bps WITHOUT losing the Sharpe gain, OR an explicit decision that lower maxDD/worst-window at equal median return is worth promoting for a risk-target sleeve (a portfolio-construction choice, not a strategy-edge choice \u2014 and Cyrus/main's call, not this vet's).",
